u don&#8217;t see a lot of 17-year-olds hacking on healthtech in their bedr=
oom.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Specifically, in healthtech, the challenge is that t=
here are thousands of EHRs that are tiny, fragmented, and antiquated, many =
of which don&#8217;t have APIs at all. That means there&#8217;s no one Syst=
em of Record, or source of truth, that anyone building products can tap int=
o to understand everything about a patient. Your dental records may be hidd=
en in one system, primary care records in another, hospital records in anot=
her, insurance information elsewhere, and so on. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a=
1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">NexHealth exi=
sts to fix that. If NexHealth is successful, in a decade or even longer, a =
new generation of entrepreneurs will be able to build healthtech products a=
s easily as they&#8217;re able to build fintech products today.&nbsp;</p><p=
 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1=
